Software Architecture-

Question13- What is the significance of modularity in software architecture?
Answer- 
Modularity is the practice of dividing a software system into smaller, independent parts called modules. Each module performs a specific function and can be developed and maintained separately.

Significance of Modularity
1. Easier Maintenance
Changes in one module do not affect the entire system
Bugs can be fixed quickly

2. Improved Reusability
Modules can be reused in other projects
Saves time and development effort

3. Better Understandability
Smaller modules are easier to understand
Helps developers work more efficiently

4. Parallel Development
Different teams can work on different modules simultaneously
Speeds up development process

5. Scalability
New features can be added without affecting existing modules
System can grow easily

6. Reduced Complexity
Breaking a large system into parts makes it manageable
Simplifies design and testing

Layers in Software Architecture-

Question14- Why are layers important in software architecture?
Answer-
Layered architecture divides a software system into different layers such as presentation, business logic, and data layers. Each layer has a specific responsibility.

Importance of Layers-
1. Separation of Concerns
Each layer handles a specific task

Example: UI, logic, and data are separated

2. Easier Maintenance
Changes in one layer do not affect others
Bugs can be fixed quickly

3. Improved Scalability
Individual layers can be upgraded or scaled independently
Helps in handling large applications

4. Better Security
Sensitive operations are handled in secure layers
Access control can be applied between layers

5. Reusability
Layers (especially business logic) can be reused in different applications

6. Simplifies Development
Developers can focus on one layer at a time
Makes teamwork easier

